body.name: Corsair Vengeance RGB Pro 32GB (4x8GB) DDR4 3200MHz C16 LED Desktop Memory - Black
features: High performance DDR4 memory illuminates your system with vivid, animated lighting from ten ultra-bright, individually addressable RGB LEDs per module.
Take control with CORSAIR iCUE software and synchronize lighting across all your CORSAIR iCUE compatible products, including memory, fans, coolers, keyboards and more.
Customize lighting profiles with millions of different patterns and colors, or create your own in CORSAIR iCUE software.
Compatible with Intel and AMD DDR4 motherboards.
Requires no extra wires or cables for a clean and seamless install.
Custom performance PCB for the highest signal quality and performance stability.
Carefully screened ICs for extended overclocking potential.
Built-in aluminum heat spreader provides superb memory cooling even when overclocked.
Supports Intel XMP 2.0 for simple one-setting installation and optimum performance.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast memory and it looks good!
reviews.reviewText: - I have a white theme computer and it looks so fresh!- Memory detected right away- I video edit and do a lot of gaming- No slowdowns or hiccups! I have both DDR4-3200 and DDR4-4400 from difference computers i don't feel any difference. Faster memory will not necessarily make your system faster. You can't speed up your computer by adding faster memory. Upgrading your NVME SSD/CPU/GPU will make it faster.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Memory After Replaced Bad Module
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I chose this memory for Corsair's reputation, the price point, and for a new gaming PC build that I had to budget all other components. I started with purchase of two 4GB modules and was going to double that in a month or two. I would have loved to get faster timings, but the prices just went sky hi. After installing the two 4Gb modules, assembly of the rest of the PC with all brand new components, the PC booted perfectly, windows 10 installed easily and quickly (under 15 minutes to desktop!). I used the computer for about a day and a half installing my programs, just enjoying getting things back up to speed.Then I noticed that my games crashed. A few minutes later a dread BSOD and another. Things were getting obviously unstable, so I checked Event Log (useless unless one has the time to run and troubleshoot dozens of possibilities). Started to panic until somewhere I read to check memory, using Prime95. Having built PC's in the past, and similar experiences with bad modules, Long story short with both modules I got over 10,000 errors and the test aborted automatically. I then ran Prime95 test with 1 module at a time, and found the trouble maker. 1 module was error free after over 1 hour running the test, the second module was toast.Just to be sure, I booted up Windows with the 'good' 4GB RAM and used my PC for a couple hours with no issues whatsoever. So I contacted Amazon and arranged a return. I wasn't aware they would just send me a replacement FIRST and ask me to return the defective part AFTER, so I just purchased a replacement then called them. I didn't want to be 'down' for two days without any memory.Turns out I now have 16 Gb of RAM instead of 8. Works perfectly BTW and I am very happy, I don't yet overclock so no comments but will eventually play around with it.Happy with Amazon's customer service, I understand even brand new parts can 'hiccup' so still offering up 5 stars based on reliability after the replacement. This PC, see specs below, is awesome fast. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality RAM, works with my B450 Motherboard!
reviews.reviewText: When I initially was looking for RAM, I was going to go with the previous version of this RAM because it was on the QVL from MSI. I'm so glad I took the risk on these, listened to the reviews about these sticks working on AMD boards, and bought these for my first build. The LEDs are stunning and look amazing. I honestly have kept them at the stock color effect, and I didn't even think I was going to like that effect the most! It perfectly compliments my Cryorig H7 cooler with the white fan because it reflects the colors off of it.I did run into one issue initially. I was trying to overclock them to the A-XMP speed that my motherboard, MSI B450 Tomahawk, allowed (which is 2933 for the 3000mhz sticks). For some reason, I was getting issues where it would not go to the rated speeds. I went to the Corsair Reddit and submitted a post about it. Got feedback from one of the mods to try switching the RAM and using them individually. At first, I thought I had a dead stick because the system did not post. I later reinstalled the stick into the motherboard because I wanted to keep the colors running. Turns out I just needed to switch the RAM to the other's slot, which was odd. Not sure if it was a RAM problem or a motherboard problem. Point is, it works now. It recognized that I had 16GB usable and installed, and I was able to activate A-XMP and it posted immediately with that overclock. Works like a charm.Another note: as of this review, I've had zero problems with MSI Mystic Light working with Corsair iCue software. I use iCue to run the lighting effects on the RAM, and Mystic light for my motherboard and my RGB front fans.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Impressive Performance and Aesthetic Appeal - A Solid 5-Star Choice!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I recently upgraded my gaming rig's memory to the Corsair Vengeance RGB PRO 16 GB kit (2 x 8 GB) DDR4 3000 MHz C15, and I'm absolutely thrilled with the results. This kit delivers on both performance and aesthetics, making it a perfect choice for enthusiasts and gamers alike.The memory modules are rock-solid performers, with a clock speed of 3000 MHz and a low CAS latency of C15. This translates into snappy responsiveness and smooth multitasking, which are crucial for gaming and content creation. I've noticed a significant improvement in loading times and overall system responsiveness, making my gaming experience much more enjoyable.What sets this kit apart, however, is the mesmerizing RGB lighting. The customizable lighting effects are a treat for the eyes and allow for seamless integration with the rest of my RGB setup. Corsair's iCUE software provides an easy and intuitive way to fine-tune the lighting to match my setup's aesthetics perfectly.Installation was a breeze; the modules fit snugly into my motherboard, and XMP profiling worked flawlessly to achieve the advertised speeds without any manual tweaking required.Corsair's build quality shines through as well. The heat spreaders not only keep the modules cool but also add to the overall aesthetics. The kit feels sturdy and well-made, which is something I value in any PC component.In conclusion, the Corsair Vengeance RGB PRO 16 GB kit is a top-tier choice for anyone looking to enhance their system's performance and visual appeal. The combination of impressive speed, low latency, and captivating RGB lighting make it a clear winner in its category. If you're in the market for high-quality RAM that delivers on all fronts, this kit should be at the top of your list. A solid 5-star product without a doubt!
